<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-803-662  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 803 662.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 27 1990 v4 n31 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NIMH builds data base of mental illness. (the US NationalInstitute of Mental Health)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Richardson, Jennifer.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH) is creating adatabase of genealogical information on families with histories ofmental illness in an attempt to find genetic links to suchdisorders as Alzheimer's disease, schizophrenia and depression.andO;The NIMH will fund 10 remote diagnostic centers that will reportand upload information to a single data collection site as thefirst phase of the Molecular Genetic Initiative; the firstmaladies to be studied will be schizophrenia, Alzheimer's diseaseand bi-polar disorder, a manic-depressive condition.andP;  Projectcoordinator David Shore says that each of the three disordersinvolves genetic predisposition; families with more than oneafflicted member will be interviewed, and a subset of genealogicaldata will be submitted to a cell repository center for furtherstudy, including blood sample analysis.andP;  The database will beheadquartered at SRA Technologies Inc and will reside on Compaqcomputers running the Oracle DBMS.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data BasesGenealogyMental IllnessNational GovernmentGovernment AgencyPlanningUnited States. National Institute of Mental Health.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>